00:43:43.340 --> 00:43:45.340
Kim Yung Seun [assumed spelling].

00:43:45.340 --> 00:43:51.150
She is a performing artist from
North Korea now in South Korea.

00:43:51.150 --> 00:43:54.820
Yung Seun was a choreographer
and dancer until 1970

00:43:54.820 --> 00:43:57.980
when she was married and
started raising children.

00:43:57.980 --> 00:44:01.450
This was during the
Kim Il Sung's rule.

00:44:01.450 --> 00:44:05.340
One day the authorities arrested
and took away her husband.

00:44:05.340 --> 00:44:06.860
A month later, she was taken

00:44:06.860 --> 00:44:11.150
to a national security agency
building for interrogation.

00:44:11.150 --> 00:44:13.720
There, she was told to
write a notebook everything

00:44:13.720 --> 00:44:16.830
about her life and
everyone she knew.

00:44:16.830 --> 00:44:20.800
After two months, she and
her family, her parents

00:44:20.800 --> 00:44:22.160
and four children were sent

00:44:22.160 --> 00:44:25.070
to a concentration camp called
Yodak [assumed spelling].

00:44:25.070 --> 00:44:27.680
Her parents died of malnutrition.

00:44:27.680 --> 00:44:30.940
One son was shot and
killed trying to escape.

00:44:30.940 --> 00:44:33.950
And another son was left on
the ground outside of her home

00:44:33.950 --> 00:44:37.040
in the camp, dead from drowning.

00:44:37.040 --> 00:44:40.720
After nine years, she and
her two surviving children,

00:44:40.720 --> 00:44:44.600
a son and daughter, were released.

00:44:44.600 --> 00:44:49.410 position:56%
She adopted out her teenage daughter
to a farmer for a better life.

00:44:49.410 --> 00:44:53.550
Years later, she learned why she
was sent to the concentration camp.

00:44:53.550 --> 00:44:57.530
She knew a secret that no one
was to know, which she revealed

00:44:57.530 --> 00:45:00.340
in those interrogation notes.

00:45:00.340 --> 00:45:01.990
She was friends with an actress

00:45:01.990 --> 00:45:05.400
who had become the
mistress of Kim Yun Il.

00:45:05.400 --> 00:45:08.310
And who later gave birth to a son

00:45:08.310 --> 00:45:11.240
who by the way is today's
North Korean's dictator,

00:45:11.240 --> 00:45:14.730
Kim Yun Un's older half brother.

00:45:14.730 --> 00:45:19.040
15 years since her release from the
Yoda concentration camp, Yung Seun

00:45:19.040 --> 00:45:22.850
and her son escaped, finding
the way to South Korea.

00:45:22.850 --> 00:45:26.230
There, she wrote a book and then
choreographed a dance as part

00:45:26.230 --> 00:45:30.420
of a theater production of
the Yoda concentration camp.

00:45:30.420 --> 00:45:35.340
When I asked Yung Seun now in
her 70's how she can survive

00:45:35.340 --> 00:45:41.510
so much pain and loss, she said
that every day she embraces freedom

00:45:41.510 --> 00:45:43.950
and every moment of life.

00:45:43.950 --> 00:45:46.540
Yung Seun is a human
rights activist fighting

00:45:46.540 --> 00:45:49.440
for the rights of North Koreans.

00:45:49.440 --> 00:45:53.030
Tarika Kenneth Desiree [assumed
spelling] is a performing artist

00:45:53.030 --> 00:45:54.940
living in Uganda.

00:45:54.940 --> 00:45:58.590
Today, Ugandans are
experiencing increased oppression

00:45:58.590 --> 00:46:02.720
with the parliament passing a law
allowing police more power while

00:46:02.720 --> 00:46:05.250
restricting people's rights.

00:46:05.250 --> 00:46:09.460
People are not allowed to gather
in public places or express dissent

00:46:09.460 --> 00:46:12.220
or criticism of their government.

00:46:12.220 --> 00:46:16.000
Police may use firearms to
shoot and kill protestors

00:46:16.000 --> 00:46:19.110
and bystanders in demonstrations.

00:46:19.110 --> 00:46:23.020
Media outlets are targeted and
closed down and threats are made

00:46:23.020 --> 00:46:25.070
against civil society groups

00:46:25.070 --> 00:46:29.840
and journalists whose work involve
government policy and human rights,

00:46:29.840 --> 00:46:32.510
particularly the rights
of lesbian, gay,

00:46:32.510 --> 00:46:36.600
bisexual and transgender people.

00:46:36.600 --> 00:46:39.420
Tarika shared examples of
how the mandate was used

00:46:39.420 --> 00:46:41.830
against people where he lives.

00:46:41.830 --> 00:46:46.800
In 20 -- I'm sorry, in June, 2010,
Tarika was part of an audience

00:46:46.800 --> 00:46:50.640
that was watching some documentary
films in the Witoto [ph] Church

00:46:50.640 --> 00:46:56.150
about human rights when police
targeted the church and raided it,

00:46:56.150 --> 00:46:59.000
blocking the screening of
the film about the trial

00:46:59.000 --> 00:47:01.970
of the prominent leaders
of the defeated Nazis

00:47:01.970 --> 00:47:04.920
in Germany after World War II.

00:47:04.920 --> 00:47:08.140
In October, 2012, The
State of the Nation,

00:47:08.140 --> 00:47:11.690
a production by a local playwright,
John Sigarwa [assumed spelling],

00:47:11.690 --> 00:47:16.730
was deemed incisive and
a threat to patriotism.

00:47:16.730 --> 00:47:19.750
Because it highlighted
critical issues like corruption

00:47:19.750 --> 00:47:21.930
and the governance in Uganda,

00:47:21.930 --> 00:47:25.780
the play was banned
immediately after its premiere.

00:47:25.780 --> 00:47:30.440
Tarika is a professional dancer and
choreographer as well as founder

00:47:30.440 --> 00:47:33.770
of the Yeda Convicts
[ph] Dance Company.

00:47:33.770 --> 00:47:37.770
Started in 2006, Yeda
Convicts mission is

00:47:37.770 --> 00:47:40.500
to transform society through dance.

00:47:40.500 --> 00:47:42.580
Through dance, performances
communicate

00:47:42.580 --> 00:47:46.900
and educate the audiences about
the things that affect society

00:47:46.900 --> 00:47:50.810
and in Uganda there
is so much to say.

00:47:52.380 --> 00:47:56.270
We are asked a lot about what the
Judischle Kulturbund Project is

00:47:56.270 --> 00:47:58.210
doing with all that we have learned

00:47:58.210 --> 00:48:01.360
about the Kulturbund
and today's artists.

00:48:01.360 --> 00:48:05.490
Well, I'd love to share
some of what we're doing.

00:48:05.490 --> 00:48:08.840
In collaboration with an
extraordinary creative team

00:48:08.840 --> 00:48:15.370
and supportive scholars and
advisors, we are producing Playing

00:48:15.370 --> 00:48:19.510
for Life, Art Under Tyranny, a
multimedia play we hope to premiere

00:48:19.510 --> 00:48:23.520
in D.C. The production brings
together characters based

00:48:23.520 --> 00:48:26.820
on the Kulturbund and current
day artists, musicians,

00:48:26.820 --> 00:48:29.670
actors and dancers
that magically meet

00:48:29.670 --> 00:48:32.450
on stage through time and space.

00:48:32.450 --> 00:48:35.070
We have started development
of a dramatic feature film

00:48:35.070 --> 00:48:39.390
about the Kulturbund, and we
are calling it Life or Theater,

00:48:39.390 --> 00:48:42.100
which is set in Berlin
in the 1930's.

00:48:42.100 --> 00:48:43.400
As I speak right now,

00:48:43.400 --> 00:48:47.450
our screenwriter is writing
the first draft of the movie

00:48:47.450 --> 00:48:50.360
so I don't want to
reveal too much about it.

00:48:50.360 --> 00:48:53.330
We are also building
an education program.

00:48:53.330 --> 00:48:55.730
We have ideas for working
with teachers and kids

00:48:55.730 --> 00:48:59.080
that include connecting
classrooms in the U.S. and abroad

00:48:59.080 --> 00:49:01.210
where we explore issues
of oppression

00:49:01.210 --> 00:49:03.950 position:56%
and responses through art and music.

00:49:03.950 --> 00:49:08.940
We are also planning with the
[inaudible] Jewish Day School

00:49:08.940 --> 00:49:13.880 position:56%
and the Musicians for World Harmony,
a series of kids music videos.

00:49:13.880 --> 00:49:17.820
And we have an idea for a book and
exhibition that features profiles

00:49:17.820 --> 00:49:21.360
of our artists and children's
response to the artist's story

00:49:21.360 --> 00:49:24.870
through their written
word, visual art and music.

00:49:24.870 --> 00:49:28.340
We continue to find new
artists and audiences

00:49:28.340 --> 00:49:30.100
who connect with our efforts.

00:49:30.100 --> 00:49:34.340 position:56%
In September, I was in Sweden giving
a presentation at a conference

00:49:34.340 --> 00:49:37.110
about culture and freedom
