00:49:37.110 --> 00:49:40.020
While there, for a couple of weeks,

00:49:40.020 --> 00:49:42.380
we found Heda [assumed
spelling] Krauss.

00:49:42.380 --> 00:49:44.110
She is a Swedish playwright.

00:49:44.110 --> 00:49:49.680
He's storytelling to
expose oppression of women

00:49:49.680 --> 00:49:52.900
and is working ona performance
right now about the wrongs

00:49:52.900 --> 00:49:57.890
of the Roma people which
is an initiative supported

00:49:57.890 --> 00:50:00.030
by the Swedish government.

00:50:00.030 --> 00:50:03.070
And we interviewed two refugees.

00:50:03.070 --> 00:50:06.110
Hollad Herrara [assumed spelling],
a [inaudible] rapper who is working

00:50:06.110 --> 00:50:09.090
in Sweden on music programs
for kids in his homeland

00:50:09.090 --> 00:50:13.240
and is also planning
a music academy there,

00:50:13.240 --> 00:50:16.110
and Assad Budda [assumed
spelling] a [inaudible] historian

00:50:16.110 --> 00:50:21.560 position:56%
and philosopher from Afghanistan who
feels a deep affinity for Judaism,

00:50:21.560 --> 00:50:26.540
and was fired from a university
position in Afghanistan for sharing

00:50:26.540 --> 00:50:30.630
with his students his connection to
the Jew's history, their struggles,

00:50:30.630 --> 00:50:35.830
strong sense of identity and
ability to overcome adversity.

00:50:35.830 --> 00:50:39.540
More than 1000 fatwas have
been issued against him,

00:50:39.540 --> 00:50:42.050
and his Visa's running out.

00:50:42.050 --> 00:50:46.220
He can't return to Afghanistan
because he will be stoned to death.

00:50:46.220 --> 00:50:50.300
He told us after our interview,
"Your work is a constellatoin,

00:50:50.300 --> 00:50:53.330
drawing stars in the dark sky.

00:50:53.330 --> 00:50:57.170
I am darkness and trying to
connect you to the Hazara artists,

00:50:57.170 --> 00:51:01.390
the starsof Afghan-Persian
dark history."

00:51:01.390 --> 00:51:08.060
Through all of our various
efforts, we will tell you the story

00:51:08.060 --> 00:51:11.140
of the Kulturbund and
those of today's artists

00:51:11.140 --> 00:51:14.770
and how they responded living
under oppression, spanning the time

00:51:14.770 --> 00:51:17.500
from 1933 to the present.

00:51:17.500 --> 00:51:21.930 position:56%
I want to thank you all for allowing
me to share the faces, the music,

00:51:21.930 --> 00:51:26.900
the art and the stories of the
artists who define our project.

00:51:26.900 --> 00:51:29.410
They motivate me every day.

00:51:29.410 --> 00:51:32.110
These artists are brave,
generous and appreciative

00:51:32.110 --> 00:51:35.360
of what we were doing
for them on our project.

00:51:35.360 --> 00:51:40.110 position:56%
We are grateful to them for allowing
us to share our stories with you.

00:51:40.110 --> 00:51:44.480 position:56%
Our project's desire is to introduce
you and others to the Kulturbund

00:51:44.480 --> 00:51:47.490
and today's artists and
show you how they respond

00:51:47.490 --> 00:51:48.810
to oppression through art.

00:51:48.810 --> 00:51:52.820
It is our hope that through the
Judische Kulturbund Project's

00:51:52.820 --> 00:51:57.100
