00:52:53.330 --> 00:52:58.640
like Gail said is Ah,
I Want to Live.

00:52:58.640 --> 00:53:00.900
This was performed by
the Judische Kulturbund

00:53:00.900 --> 00:53:04.220
in 1934, the entire opera.

00:53:04.220 --> 00:53:07.870
The first few words are I
want to live in this dream,

00:53:07.870 --> 00:53:10.880
that intoxicates me
to this day still.

00:53:10.880 --> 00:53:14.240
In our context, the Judische
Kulturbund was keeping

00:53:14.240 --> 00:53:17.220
that dream alive in the
lives of the German Jews

00:53:17.220 --> 00:53:20.540
by creating an organization
that allowed Jews to perform

00:53:20.540 --> 00:53:23.440
and experience art and
beauty through music

00:53:23.440 --> 00:53:26.020
when danger would be
lurking in every corner.

00:53:26.020 --> 00:53:29.060
It became a safe haven when
things started to get ugly,

00:53:29.060 --> 00:53:32.930
and in this piece, Juliet is
about to attend her birthday ball,

00:53:32.930 --> 00:53:37.380 position:56%
but while she's excited for her
party, she's terrified of the future

00:53:37.380 --> 00:53:41.050
and growing up, of possibly
falling in love or being forced

00:53:41.050 --> 00:53:44.010
to marry a man that
she doesn't love.

00:53:44.010 --> 00:53:46.440
She's afraid to leave her
happy childhood behind

00:53:46.440 --> 00:53:51.500
for an uncertain future just as
many Jews in Germany were reluctant

00:53:51.500 --> 00:53:54.090
to leave their former lives behind.

00:53:54.090 --> 00:53:57.800
This aria also speaks to
the millions of people

00:53:57.800 --> 00:54:00.780
around the world today who are
living in oppression who just want

00:54:00.780 --> 00:54:04.770
to choose love and happiness.

